<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871001-0082 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:MMR Holding Corp.</HL><DD> 10/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MMRHJUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS) </IN><DATELINE> BATON ROUGE  </DATELINE><TEXT>   MMR Holding Corp. said it was told by the Justice Department that the company's president, James Rutland, and its Matthews-McCracken-Rutland Corp. unit are the focus of a federal grand jury investigation of bid-rigging allegations.    The company said Matthews-McCracken-Rutland received a subpoena from the panel, which is looking into bidding on an electrical power plant in 1981, as well as a 1977 project in which the unit was involved.    No charges have been brought against MMR Holding. The company said it is &quot;confident that the questions raised will be answered fully.&quot;    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, MMR Holding stock closed at $21.25, down 50 cents. </TEXT></DOC>